      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HENRY'S BLADE (2) peaks off narrow defeats at Townsville and over this trip at Rockhampton following in a strong form race. Has the gate speed to skip across and sit handy, and it's hard to risk the potent Wiggins-Taylor linkage. Tough to beat. ANSWERING (7) found one much too good well supported at Rockhampton last time, but stalked the lead here prior, beaten a whisker over 1100m in Open grade. Carries 4kg less today and Cormack is reunited. He will push forward and should be right in it. SCRUB CHAIN (4) peaks and has been racing in Open class at Rochhampton. Carries more weight but maps well and presents fourth-up. Has to be considered. DEALING'S DONE (6) resumes and will be competitive if presented on song.",
